25 LC 61 0004
House Bill 694
By: Representatives Lupton of the 83rd, Lim of the 98th, and Wilkerson of the 38th
A BILL TO BE ENTITLED
AN ACT
1 To amend Article 14 of Chapter 2 of Title 20 of the Official Code of Georgia Annotated,
2 relating to elementary and secondary education grants, so as to provide for the State Board
3 of Education to establish a five-year school pilot program to increase the availability of
4 effective school counseling and postsecondary preparation services in secondary schools to
5 increase high school graduation rates and the percentage of students who continue into
6 postsecondary education; to provide for eligibility; to provide for grant funds for local
7 education agencies to increase the availability of effective school counseling at public
8 secondary schools; to provide for applications and selection to participate in the pilot
9 program; to provide for assessment and reporting on the impacts of the pilot program; to
10 authorize the State Board of Education to promulgate rules and regulations necessary to
11 implement the pilot program; to provide for waivers and variances of state rules, regulations,
12 policies, and procedures if necessary; to provide for automatic repeal; to provide for related
13 matters; to provide for an effective date; to repeal conflicting laws; and for other purposes.
14 BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF GEORGIA:
