15 SECTION 1.
16 Article 14 of Chapter 2 of Title 20 of the Official Code of Georgia Annotated, relating to
17 elementary and secondary education grants, is amended by revising Code Section 20-2-640,
18 which is reserved, as follows:
19 "20-2-640.
20 (a) As used in this Code section, the term:
21 (1) 'Local education agency' shall have the same meaning as provided for in Code
22 Section 20-2-167.1.
23 (2) 'Local governing body' means the local board of education, governing board, or other
24 legal entity responsible for the governance and oversight of a local education agency.
25 (3) 'Participating school' means a public secondary school identified by the State Board
26 of Education or local governing body as participating in the pilot program.
27 (4) 'Postsecondary institution' shall have the same meaning as 'eligible postsecondary
28 institution' as defined in Code Section 20-3-519.
29 (5) 'School counselor' means an individual who holds a service certificate in School
30 Counseling P-12 issued by the Georgia Professional Standards Commission.
31 (b) The State Board of Education shall establish a pilot program to provide funding to
32 eligible local education agencies to increase the availability of effective school counseling
33 and postsecondary preparation services in secondary schools with the goal of increasing
34 the graduation rate within the state and increasing the percentage of students who
35 appropriately prepare for, apply to, and continue into postsecondary education.
36 (c) Subject to appropriations by the General Assembly, the pilot program shall include
37 funding for up to $3 million each school year, for up to five school years, beginning with
38 the 2027-2028 school year, to eligible local education agencies selected by the State Board
39 of Education to participate in the pilot program.
40 (d) To be eligible to participate in the pilot program, a local education agency shall submit
41 an application to participate in the pilot program, which application shall include:
